        <p class="article-lead">Argumentative Relation Identification (ARI) is a subtask of Argument Mining (AM) and aims at classifying if a given source Argumentative Discourse Unit (ADU) supports, attacks, or is unrelated to a second ADU <a href="https://aclanthology.org/D15-1110/">[Peldszus and Stede, 2015]</a>.</p>
