      <div class="article-content ps-lg-4">
        <h2 class="mt-5">Task</h2>
        <p>
            ARI is a classification task that is a subtask of the Argument Mining task. Argument mining is research area with the goal of
            automatically extract and identify argumentative structures. The ARI subtask consists of determining, for two sentences
            with argumentative content (also known as Argumentative Discourse Units), whether the first attacks, supports, or is unrelated 
            to the second. The first sentence is known as Source ADU and the second as Target ADU.
        </p>
        <p>
            Since it is a classification task, the model uses the output corresponding to the <em>[CLS]</em> to make the prediction. The prediction is done
            with a Feed Forward neural network and a <a href="https://machinelearningmastery.com/softmax-activation-function-with-python/">softmax layer</a>,
            giving the confidence of each possible classification label.
        </p>
